llenerfüllungen (re-)präsentiert werden. Damit bietet ihre Studie einen Einblick in die Bedeutung der Drogenkriminalität für das Leben in den Grenzstädten Mexikos.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrug trafficzMexicoxSongs and music. 0aDrugs in popular music. 0aOrganized crimezMexico. 0aRap (Music)zMexican-American Border Region. 4aArmut. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDrogenkrieg. 4aGrenze. 4aKriminalität. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLateinamerika. 4aMexiko. 4aMusik. 4aOrganisiertes Verbrechen. 4aPopkultur. 4aPopmusik. 4aRaum. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aBorder.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aDrug War.  aLatin America.  aMexico.  aMusic.  aOrganised Crime.  aPop Music.  aPopular Culture.  aPoverty.  aSpace.2 aBacklisttransformation EOSC Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2021z9783111025100oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839460375?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839460375zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839460375/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-2